'''Muhammad ibn Isa''' was a [[Khorasan|Khurasani]] warrior who came to Aleppo some time around the spring of 967 with around 5,000 soldiers in order to engage in a [[Jihad|''jihad]] against the [[Byzantine Empire]]. While the Byzantine emperor, [[Nikephoros II Phokas]], was campaigning against the [[First Bulgarian Empire|Bulgarians]] in the west, Isa managed to secure a victory against the Byzantines and advanced into [[Cilicia]].{{sfn|PmbZ|loc=Muḥammad b. Eesa(#25440)}} Nikephoros sent [[Peter (stratopedarches)|Petros]] to challenge Isa, where he defeated him around [[Alexandretta]] in 968.{{sfn|PmbZ|loc=Petros (#26496)}} Petros then ransomed Isa to the people of [[Antioch]] in exchange for Byzantine prisoners of war.{{sfn|Kaldellis|2017|p=61}}{{sfn|PmbZ|loc=Muḥammad b. Eesa(#25440)}}

