{{about|traveling jurists||Circuit rider (disambiguation)|Circuit rider}} '''Riding circuit''' is the practice of judges and lawyers, sometimes referred to as '''circuit riders''', travelling to a regular series of locations in order to hold court there, {{cns|date=November 2017|perhaps once a week or once a month.}} {{cns|date=November 2017|Traveling judges are now rare,}} but the term remains in the name "[[circuit court]]", commonly applied to levels of court that oversee many lower district courts.
==See also== * [[Assizes]] &mdash; a type of judicial courts, to which "riding circuit" often applied * [[Circuit court]] &mdash; a type of judicial courts, to which "riding circuit" often applied * [[Itinerant court]] &mdash; older, similar concept for royalty and governments
