'''Thinset''' (also called '''thinset mortar''', '''thinset cement''', '''dryset mortar''', or '''drybond mortar''') is an [[adhesive]] [[mortar (masonry)|mortar]] made of [[portland cement|cement]], fine [[sand]] and a water retaining agent such as an [[alkyl]] derivative of [[cellulose]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mastic vs Thinset &#8211; Which should I use?|url=https://www.tiletools.com/mastic-vs-thinset-use/|website=Tile Tools|accessdate=14 June 2014}}</ref> It is usually used to attach [[ceramic tile|tile]] or [[Rock (geology)|stone]] to surfaces such as cement or [[concrete]]. It is particularly popular among [[mosaic|mosaicists]] for outdoor applications <ref>{{cite web|title=Thinset Mortar for Mosaic Artwork|website=Mosaic Art Supply|url=http://www.mosaicartsupply.com/thinset-glass-mosaic-tile.aspx|accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>
