{{notability|date=March 2012}} {{unreferenced|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox journal | title = Utrecht Journal of International and European Law | editor = Karolina Aksamitowska | discipline = [[Law]] | language = English | abbreviation = Utrecht J. Int. Eur. Law | publisher = [[Ubiquity Press]] | frequency = Biannually | history = 1981-present | openaccess = Yes | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.utrechtjournal.org | link2 = http://www.utrechtjournal.org/issue/archive/ | link2-name = Online archive (2010–present) | cover = | formernames = Merkourios | JSTOR = | OCLC = 864417242 | LCCN = 2015269181 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0927-460X | eISSN = 2053-5341 }} The '''''Utrecht Journal of International and European Law''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[law review|law journal]] covering [[International law|international]] and [[European Union law|European law]]. It is affiliated with [[Utrecht University]] and [[Urios]].
The journal was established in 1981 as a student [[magazine]] titled ''Merkourios'', containing summaries of study-trips, conferences, and other issues related to Urios, an association for international and European law. Since then it has evolved from a magazine into a formal, academic law journal. This development was finalised in 2009, when peer-review was officially integrated into the reviewing process. The journal obtained its current name in 2013, and is published by [[Ubiquity Press]].[http://www.ubiquitypress.com/site/journals/]
A complete log of all previous issues is hosted by [[HeinOnline]].[http://home.heinonline.org/titles/Law-Journal-Library/Utrecht-Journal-of-International-and-European-Law/?letter=U]
